1. Assemble the Circuit

Connect sensors to Arduino input pins.

Connect lights/fan to relay modules.

Provide regulated 5V/12V supply to sensors.

Connect LM35 to analog pin.

2. Upload the Code

Load the provided Arduino sketch into the Arduino IDE.

Verify and upload to microcontroller.

3. Testing

Move in front of PIR to check automatic light switching.

Heat LM35 sensor (e.g., by touching) to check fan control.

Test IR sensor for entry detection.
